During a high-pressure soccer match between the Manchester United and Arsenal, both teams were tied 1-1 with only a few minutes left on the clock. As the ball was passed around midfield, Arsenal's star player, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, shouted to his teammate, "Pass it to me! Pass it to me!"
However, due to the loud cheering of the fans, his teammate misheard him and thought he said, "Pass it to the ref! Pass it to the ref!" So, without hesitation, he kicked the ball towards the referee who was standing near the sideline.
The crowd erupted in laughter as the referee looked confused and quickly moved out of the way of the ball. Aubameyang, realizing what had happened, put his hands on his head in disbelief while his teammate hung his head in shame.
In the end, the match ended in a draw, but the players and fans will always remember the hilarious miscommunication that occurred on the field.
